item.description:
Extension: smart Interpret straight quotes as curly quotes, --- as em-dashes, -- as en-dashes, and ... as ellipses. Nonbreaking spaces are inserted after certain abbreviations, such as &ldquo;Mr.&rdquo;
This extension can be enabled/disabled for the following formats:
input formats markdown, commonmark, latex, mediawiki, org, rst, twiki output formats markdown, latex, context, rst enabled by default in markdown, latex, context (both input and output) Note: If you are writing Markdown, then the smart extension has the reverse effect: what would have been curly quotes comes out straight.
